items.title: Forensic Files
items.description: An infant was rushed to a Cleveland emergency room with serious breathing problems. The baby's lungs were bleeding. Within months, there were more than 30 cases -- an incidence more than a thousand times higher than anywhere else in the world. Doctors had never seen anything like it, and searched frantically for the cause and a cure.

seasons.description: Between 1985 and 1988, 18 people were choked, molested and left for dead in the remote desert mountains of California. The only witnesses were the insects - and they also proved to play an important role in solving the crimes and bringing the killer to justice.

In a quiet village in Great Britain, a farmer came upon a chilling sight. Impaled on his fence post was a severed lamb's head along with a note which read, "You next." The author of the note didn't elaborate on why the farmer had been targeted, but between the lines, he'd said plenty.

items.title: Unsolved Mysteries With Robert Stack
items.description: This episode includes: Coma Comeback, Update: Two Strikes, Palm Beach Embezzler, Twice Burned and Fumbles & UD.

seasons.description: This episode includes: Pizza Man & UD, The Dale & UD, Update: Mrs. Millionaire and Teri's Killer.
This episode includes: Christmas Party Murder, Update: Nudist Fraud, Gypsy Fraud, Drummond's Dollars & UD and Coma Recovery.

items.title: Road To Race Day
items.description: Chase Elliott and the Number 24 team experience growing pains as they race to the checkered flag amidst the roar of NASCAR's biggest crowd.

items.title: On the Ropes
items.description: Aspiring boxing trainer Amirah Al-Amir secures a pro debut fight for competitor Jess O'Connor.

items.title: Thanksgiving
items.description: A dysfunctional family gathers together during the Thanksgiving holiday weekend.

items.title: Animal Tales
items.description: A show for pet lovers and animal advocates that will enlighten and inspire viewers of all ages to embrace the unconditional love between humans and their animals. Animal Tales will inspire people to love their pets more than ever before.

items.title: Kitchen Nightmares
items.description: Celebrity chef and Michelin Star winner Gordon Ramsay travels across America attempting to turn failing restaurants into sought after venues.

items.title: Hidden Heroes
items.description: Inspired by the best selling Chicken Soup for the Soul book series.

items.title: Defenders of the Earth
items.description: Flash Gordon, the Phantom, Mandrake the Magician and Lothar, with help from their children, join forces to protect Earth from Ming the Merciless.

items.title: Hunter
items.description: When Rick Hunter, a renegade cop who takes justice into his own hands, partners with the stunning and rebellious Sgt. McCall, they set out to crack down on L.A.'s slimiest criminals.

items.title: Americas Greatest Unsolved Mysteries and Crimes
items.description: America's Masonic conspiracy. The strange mysteries of the Anasazi. What really happened to Amelia Earhart? Who kidnapped the Lindbergh baby?

items.title: Little Angels
items.description: LITTLE ANGELS follows the daily adventures of Alex and Zoe, twin preschoolers who, like other kids their age, need lots of help understanding their place in the world and the difference between right and wrong.

items.title: Penance
items.description: Directed by Japanese master Kiyoshi Kurosawa, Penance is an intense tale of obsession and revenge which opens with the startling, mysterious murder of school girl Emili, and follows the life trajectories of the four girls who were present at the scene of the crime, as they become adults and must bear the burden of the tragedy imposed on them by Emili's grieving mother.

items.title: Fight Club: A History of Violence
items.description: A show that follows human conflict throughout the ages.

items.title: Barney Google and Snuffy Smith
items.description: There's feudin', fussin' and a whole lot of good ol' fashioned fun goin' on as those back woods rascals, Barney Google and Snuffy Smith, rustle up a rib-ticklin' tub of mountain mirth.

items.title: Cool McCool
items.description: A suave yet bumbling secret agent fights an array of heinous villains.

items.title: Animated All Star Specials
items.description: Classic cartoon characters dating back to the 1930s are featured in this compilation, including Betty Boop, Beetle Bailey, Blondie & Dagwood, and Hagar the Horrible.

items.title: 21 Jump Street
items.description: To combat crime in schools, the LAPD decides to send four young cops to high school to pose as students. Officers Tom Hanson, Doug Penhall, Judy Hoffs and Harry Truman Ioki are the lucky ones chosen to experience the part of their lives they hoped they had left behind forever.

items.title: Hells Kitchen
items.description: Gordon Ramsay hosts a fiery cooking competition in which the winner receives a head chef position.

items.title: Dance Academy
items.description: Small-town teenager Tara Webster dreams of becoming a ballet dancer at the National Academy of Dance. Tara and her fellow students push themselves as relationships grow while the teens live with one another in the school's boarding house.

items.title: Professor Green
items.description: Are white, working class men in modern Britain suffering an identity crisis? Rapper turned documentary filmmaker Professor Green follows the lives of 6 men over a period of 6 months to explore some of the issues they face.

items.title: Speed with Guy Martin
items.description: Motorcycle racer and mechanic Guy Martin undertakes a series of speed-based challenges, exploring the boundaries of physics and learning about the science of speed.

items.title: Beaver Falls
items.description: Three British students decided to spend their summer in an American summer camp and make a large impression on fellow camp workers and the campers.

items.title: 3rd Rock from the Sun
items.description: The high commander of an alien expedition lands on Earth -- what he considers to be the least-important planet -- in human form as Dick Solomon. Along for the ride are his alien compatriots Harry, Sally and Tommy -- who is the eldest of the group but is now angrily trapped in a teen's body.

items.title: Super Sentai Zyuranger
items.description: A closeknit band of teenagers living in Japan transforms into a uniformed team of superheroes ready to take on any villains. Their primary focus is Rita Repulsa, a space villainess bent on world domination -- presented by Shout! Factory TV

items.title: Heirloom
items.description: When down-on-her-luck actress Emily comes into an unlikely inheritance, she moves to Sonoma to re-invent herself as a tomato farmer. Her new tomato farm soon yields new friends, new business, and a new shot at love.

items.title: My Classic Car
items.description: Come honor classic automobiles with host Dennis Gage! Explore car shows and exhibits across America, Canada, and the UK as Dennis Looks for classic cars that have withstood the test of time.

items.title: Ruby Gloom
items.description: Some kids might be afraid of the dark. But Ruby is different: she befriends strange characters like Doom Kitty, Skull Boy, Misery, Boo Boo and Mr Buns.

items.title: Sam and Max
items.description: Sam the dog and Max the rabbit's adventures.

items.title: Adventures of Flash Gordon
items.description: Flash Gordon must defend against all manner of intergalactic attackers in this space-faring adventure

items.title: My Pet Monster
items.description: Max must hide his pet monster from his family and friends

items.title: The Legend of Prince Valiant
items.description: The medieval adventures of Price Valiant

items.title: My Dad the Rockstar
items.description: Willy must learn who he is and deal with his dad being a rock star.

items.title: Maggie and the Ferocious Beast
items.description: Maggie, Hamilton and the Beast are having great fun in the snow, making snow sculptures and snow angels, and throwing snowballs. Hamilton's box makes a very good sled, until it hits a rock and is torn. Hamilton is filled with remorse, and sings a sad little song about his beloved box. Maggie eventually saves the day, fixing the tear with one of the Beast's spots.

items.title: The New Adventures of Flash Gordon
items.description: The adventures of Flash Gordon, the space-traveling hero

items.title: Birdz
items.description: The adventures of the Birdz

items.title: Blazing Dragons
items.description: Blazing Dragons is the story of the epic adventures of knights and dragons-from the point-of-view of the dragons. Blazing Dragons tells us what really happened in the age of chivalry; how gallant, generous dragons took on the brutal, greedy humans knights to rescue damsels in distress, save the peasants from oppression and generally make the world a much more entertaining place to be in.

items.title: The Magical Adventures of Quasimodo
items.description: The magical city of Paris, 1483, is a place of gypsies, giants, dwarfs, magical spells, and secret potions. Quasimodo, Esmeralda, and Francois fight against various villains, and overcome sinister plots and deadly traps. They often face the King's greatest enemy, Frollo, a man dedicated to the pursuit of all evil.

items.title: Pet Alien
items.description: Tommy Cadle's seemingly normal life is turned upside down when a group of wild, outrageous aliens crash into his world. The outsiders take refuge in the boy's lighthouse and take over his life in the process.

items.title: Tales From the Cryptkeeper
items.description: The Cryptkeeper serves up terrifying tales to shock and scare.

items.title: Redwall
items.description: The adventures of a young mouse and his friends.

items.title: Dumb Bunnies
items.description: Momma, Poppa and Baby Dumb Bunny are three hapless hares whose world is filled with blissful ignorance.

items.title: Di Gata Defenders
items.description: Only one group can control the destiny of the powerful Di-Gata Stones, and with the help of the Guardian creatures, four teenage warriors -- Seth, Melosa, Erik and Kara -- are entrusted with finding the pure gems to save the good people of RaDos against the villainous Order of Infinis.

items.title: Project Dad
items.description: Being a parent in today's fast paced world is challenging. Being a celebrity parent is in a world of its own.  In this groundbreaking new series, PROJECT DAD will turn the camera on three busy celebrity fathers as they put their self-focusing careers on the sidelines and get to know their children like never before. The celebrity dads will be tasked with "full responsibility" of looking after their young children while mom takes a break. The dads will dive in, no help and no mercy!

items.title: Life On The Line
items.description: Against All Odds

items.title: Betrayal
items.description: Behind Edwin Wilson's charming exterior lay a man deep in the world of illicit arms smuggling and international mercenaries. At the time of his arrest, Wilson was the United States most wanted fugitive in the world- or was he in fact, a CIA operative?

items.title: The Saint
items.description: Simon Templar (played by Roger Moore) is a wealthy adventurer known as The Saint. He travels around the world in his white Volvo P1800S, helping those who can't be helped by conventional means and always staying one step ahead of the law -- presented by Shout! Factory TV

items.title: The Weird Al Show
items.description: An educational and comedic show where "Weird Al" Yankovic must deal with different and interesting people who come to his crazy house -- presented by Shout! Factory TV

items.title: Keys to the VIP
items.description: "Cocoa Butter" Chris goes against Yakov "The Trapper" for the keys to the VIP.

items.title: Wilfred
items.description: The story of an unhappy, talking, drug-using dog and its owner -- presented by Shout! Factory TV

items.title: The Book Group
items.description: Magical Realism. Kenny is writing a book in which his character shares a mountain cabin with a beautiful woman who looks just like Fist whilst Clare is also writing a novel.

items.title: Chef School
items.description: It's Christmas. The students present a special holiday surprise. Jim and Eleanor do Christmas - eggnog, rum balls, tourtiere and, of course, the proper way to decorate the tree.

items.title: Girly Ghost Hunters
items.description: The Bytown Museum, Ottawa's oldest stone building houses the capital's history, as well as some of its ghosts! Take the tour with The Girly Ghosthunters, and stay for a little afterhours paranormal fun as the lights go out and scares begin.

items.title: Urban Legends
items.description: A series which dramatises 3-4 well-known urban legends each episode. The catch is one (or more) of the 'legends' actually did happen, and it's for the viewer to figure it out.

items.title: The Goode Family
items.description: An animated TV program that revolves around a family obsessed with doing the "right" thing environmentally, politically and socially -- presented by Shout! Factory TV

items.title: Sonic the Hedgehog
items.description: Sonic conquers Robotnik's latest evil, a vehicle designated to locate and destroy living tissue matter, during a solo mission to the Badlands.

items.title: Coast Guard Alaska
items.description: The captain races to the North Pole; two helicopter rescue crews go on a mission to save injured fishermen; an aerial search is launched for a missing person in the North Pacific.

items.title: Untamed with Davey Hughes
items.description: Davey Hughes Untamed follows the extraordinary journeys of New Zealander Davey Hughes, as he embarks on nine very different and challenging voyages in some of the most spectacular, far-flung corners of the globe.

items.title: Maison Close
items.description: Paris, 1871. This is a story of the women trapped in a luxury brothel, 'Paradise'. The ladies trapped in Paradise must deal with their individual problems while navigating the dangerous underground world of Paris.

items.title: Flea Bitten
items.description: Fresh out of the pound and with the dog catchers hot on their tails Flea-bag and Itch find themselves exploring the big city, but when a visit to Milton's Black sausage factory sends Itch. E into a spin it leaves Flea-bag all alone to search for his family. Without Itch.

items.title: Inspector Gadget
items.description: Inspector Gadget's mission is to guard a priceless coin collection from the evil clutches of M.A.D.

items.title: Prison Families
items.description: Rob and Gail are convinced their son is innocent and shouldn't be in prison.  They spend two hundred thousand dollars trying to prove he didn't do it.

items.title: Big Comfy Couch
items.description: In the 7th season premiere, Loonette and Major Bedhead learn that healthy foods are important. At Granny's Cooking School, Loonette, Molly, and Granny make Apple Muffins.

items.title: Musti
items.description: Musti helps his neighborhood animals as he travels through his land.

items.title: Umigo
items.description: An animated TV show that teaches children math in fun and creative ways.

items.title: Chillers
items.description: Based on the short story by Patricia Highsmith, previously adapted as a feature film by Samuel Fuller.

items.title: Legend of Zelda
items.description: Based on the popular Nintendo game of the same name. Link and Princess Zelda protect the mystical artifact, the Triforce of Wisdom, from falling into the hands of the evil sorcerer Ganon.

items.title: Coast Guard Florida
items.description: Air Station Clearwater and Station Key West respond to distress calls from two different cruise ships. Down in Miami, aspiring members of the Coast Guard's Tactical Law Enforcement Team take on rigorous training. And Guardsmen from Marathon help out on a special environmental mission.

items.title: Knights Of Mayhem
items.description: After a half-year hiatus, The Black Knight Patrick Lambke returns to the list to face arch nemesis and protege Charlie Andrews along with the rest of the Knights of Mayhem at the U.S./International Jousting Championship in Estes Park, Colorado.

items.title: Air Force one Is Down
items.description: After Air Force One is sabotaged and sent plunging into the Mediterranean, President Harriet Rowntree, is held prisoner in a remote castle hideaway. The message to the United States, free Serbian dictator Arkady Dragutin from prison within twelve hours or the President will die.

items.title: Adventures of Super Mario Bros 3
items.description: King Koopa uses a Magic Wand to turn Cheatsy, Bigmouth, Bully, and Kooky into giant Ninja Koopas so they can capture Prince Hugo the Huge and turn him into a poodle. Kootie Pie Kootie hates all the presents her family supplies at her party and demands that she be given Real World America as a gift.

items.title: Women Behind Bars
items.description: This series brings women who kill to the forefront, detailing a specific case in each episode, and then trying to answer the question of why they did what they did.

items.title: Adventures of Sonic the Hedgehog
items.description: When Tails gets trapped in the Warp of Confusion by Robotnik's cousin, Dr. Warpnik, Sonic comes to the rescue and traps Robotnik and his badniks in the warp.

items.title: The Adventures of Paddington Bear
items.description: The adventures of a polite bear from Peru that comes to England after an earthquake destroys his home.

items.title: Strawberry Shortcake
items.description: Strawberry Shortcake travels to magical Holidayland with Honey Pie Pony, searching for the perfect presents to give her friends.

items.title: Lockie Leonard
items.description: What chance have you got when your dads a cop, your mum's a frighteningly understanding parent, your brother wets the bed, your best friend's a heavy metal devotee and then you fall in love at 12 and three quarters years old. It can only mean trouble, worry, mega-embarrassment and some wild, wild times.

items.title: Dog City
items.description: Cats are mobbing into Eliot's apartment building.  And Bruno will not allow it.  This gives Eliot inspiration for his latest Ace Hart Adventure. The Cat gang has decided to take over Dog city and to run the dogs out of town. Unfortunately for them they have Bugsy Vile to contend with. Unfortunately for Bugsy, he can't get rid of them alone.

items.title: Winnipeg Comedy Festival
items.description: Why do the funniest comics have the worst luck?  Host Brent Butt joins a stellar line-up of comedians sharing their best bad luck tales.  Starring Steve Patterson, Claire Brosseau, John Hastings, K Trevor Wilson, Maureen Langan, Pete Zedlacher, and Rob Pue.

items.title: Commandos
items.description: A small group of ordinary Australians are about to take part in one of the toughest military selection courses in the world.

items.title: Sky Dancers
items.description: Breeze invites the Sky Dancers to his tribe's celebration in the desert. Angelica flirts her head off, but Breeze puts her off. Meanwhile, in the Sky Kingdom, the three Imps disguise themselves and as create havoc in each realm.

videos.description: Fresh out of the pound and with the dog catchers hot on their tails Flea-bag and Itch find themselves exploring the big city, but when a visit to Milton's Black sausage factory sends Itch. E into a spin it leaves Flea-bag all alone to search for his family. Without Itch.

videos.title: Inspector Gadget
videos.description: Inspector Gadget's mission is to guard a priceless coin collection from the evil clutches of M.A.D.

videos.title: Prison Families
videos.description: Rob and Gail are convinced their son is innocent and shouldn't be in prison.  They spend two hundred thousand dollars trying to prove he didn't do it.

videos.title: Big Comfy Couch
videos.description: In the 7th season premiere, Loonette and Major Bedhead learn that healthy foods are important. At Granny's Cooking School, Loonette, Molly, and Granny make Apple Muffins.

videos.title: Musti
videos.description: Musti helps his neighborhood animals as he travels through his land.

videos.title: Umigo
videos.description: An animated TV show that teaches children math in fun and creative ways.

videos.title: Chillers
videos.description: Based on the short story by Patricia Highsmith, previously adapted as a feature film by Samuel Fuller.

videos.title: Legend of Zelda
videos.description: Based on the popular Nintendo game of the same name. Link and Princess Zelda protect the mystical artifact, the Triforce of Wisdom, from falling into the hands of the evil sorcerer Ganon.

videos.title: Coast Guard Florida
videos.description: Air Station Clearwater and Station Key West respond to distress calls from two different cruise ships. Down in Miami, aspiring members of the Coast Guard's Tactical Law Enforcement Team take on rigorous training. And Guardsmen from Marathon help out on a special environmental mission.

videos.title: Knights Of Mayhem
videos.description: After a half-year hiatus, The Black Knight Patrick Lambke returns to the list to face arch nemesis and protege Charlie Andrews along with the rest of the Knights of Mayhem at the U.S./International Jousting Championship in Estes Park, Colorado.

videos.title: Air Force one Is Down
videos.description: After Air Force One is sabotaged and sent plunging into the Mediterranean, President Harriet Rowntree, is held prisoner in a remote castle hideaway. The message to the United States, free Serbian dictator Arkady Dragutin from prison within twelve hours or the President will die.

videos.title: Adventures of Super Mario Bros 3
videos.description: King Koopa uses a Magic Wand to turn Cheatsy, Bigmouth, Bully, and Kooky into giant Ninja Koopas so they can capture Prince Hugo the Huge and turn him into a poodle. Kootie Pie Kootie hates all the presents her family supplies at her party and demands that she be given Real World America as a gift.

videos.title: Women Behind Bars
videos.description: This series brings women who kill to the forefront, detailing a specific case in each episode, and then trying to answer the question of why they did what they did.

videos.title: Adventures of Sonic the Hedgehog
videos.description: When Tails gets trapped in the Warp of Confusion by Robotnik's cousin, Dr. Warpnik, Sonic comes to the rescue and traps Robotnik and his badniks in the warp.

videos.title: The Adventures of Paddington Bear
videos.description: The adventures of a polite bear from Peru that comes to England after an earthquake destroys his home.

videos.title: Strawberry Shortcake
videos.description: Strawberry Shortcake travels to magical Holidayland with Honey Pie Pony, searching for the perfect presents to give her friends.

videos.title: Lockie Leonard
videos.description: What chance have you got when your dads a cop, your mum's a frighteningly understanding parent, your brother wets the bed, your best friend's a heavy metal devotee and then you fall in love at 12 and three quarters years old. It can only mean trouble, worry, mega-embarrassment and some wild, wild times.

videos.title: Dog City
videos.description: Cats are mobbing into Eliot's apartment building.  And Bruno will not allow it.  This gives Eliot inspiration for his latest Ace Hart Adventure. The Cat gang has decided to take over Dog city and to run the dogs out of town. Unfortunately for them they have Bugsy Vile to contend with. Unfortunately for Bugsy, he can't get rid of them alone.

videos.title: Winnipeg Comedy Festival
videos.description: Why do the funniest comics have the worst luck?  Host Brent Butt joins a stellar line-up of comedians sharing their best bad luck tales.  Starring Steve Patterson, Claire Brosseau, John Hastings, K Trevor Wilson, Maureen Langan, Pete Zedlacher, and Rob Pue.

videos.title: Commandos
videos.description: A small group of ordinary Australians are about to take part in one of the toughest military selection courses in the world.

videos.title: Sky Dancers
videos.description: Breeze invites the Sky Dancers to his tribe's celebration in the desert. Angelica flirts her head off, but Breeze puts her off. Meanwhile, in the Sky Kingdom, the three Imps disguise themselves and as create havoc in each realm.
